<TITLE> Only skilled workers will go to Saudi Arabia: PM </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 24 (bdnews24.com)Prime minister Sheikh Hasina has told the Saudi envoy that workers with professional skills and conversant in Arabic will be sent to Saudi Arabia, according to her aide. Ambassador Abdullah Naser Al Bushairy went to meet Hasina in her office on Sunday morning, the prime minister's press secretary Abul Kalam Azad told reporters. The Saudi envoy handed Hasina a message from the Saudi king condoling her husband M A Wazed Miah's recent death. The king also sympathised with the bereaved members of the prime minister's family. Hasina told the envoy that both the Bangladeshi workers in Saudi Arabia and the Bangladeshis at home were happy to know about the outcome of her recent visit to the holy land and the fruitful discussions and decisions they had there including 'aquamah', Azad said. The ambassador expressed hope that the relation between the two countries will strengthen after her recent tour. bd
